problem: Express the value of the following expression as a fraction. $$1+\cfrac{2}{3+\cfrac{4}{5}}$$
model_solution:
Step 1: Rewrite the expression by evaluating the innermost fraction: $$1+\cfrac{2}{3+\frac{4}{5}}$$
$$=1+\cfrac{2}{\frac{15}{5}+\frac{4}{5}}$$
Step 2: Simplify the complex fraction in the numerator by adding the fractions: $$1+\cfrac{2}{\frac{15}{5}+\frac{4}{5}}$$
$$=1+\cfrac{2}{\frac{19}{5}}$$
Step 3: Simplify the expression by dividing the numerator by the denominator: $$1+\cfrac{2}{\frac{19}{5}}$$
$$=1+\frac{10}{19}$$
$$=1+\frac{10}{19}$$
$$=\frac{19}{19}+\frac{10}{19}$$
$$=1+\frac{10}{19}$$
$$=\frac{19}{19}+\frac{10}{19}$$
$$=\frac{19+10}{19}$$
$$=\frac{29}{19}$$
Step 4: Simplify the expression by adding the fractions: $$=\frac{29}{19}$$
$$=1+\frac{10}{19}$$
Step 5: Simplify the expression by adding the fractions: $$=\frac{19}{19}+\frac{10}{19}$$
$$=1+\frac{10}{19}$$
